  "prompt": "What is difference between living for work and work for living?",
  "response": "The main differences between \"living for work\" and \"work for living\" are:\n\nLiving for Work:\n1. Work becomes the central focus of life\n2. Personal identity is primarily defined by career\n3. Prioritizes professional achievements over personal well-being\n4. Often leads to burnout and stress\n5. Sacrifices personal relationships and leisure time\n6. Success is measured by professional accomplishments\n7. Work dominates emotional and mental energy\n\nWork for Living:\n1. Work is a means to support life's goals and desires\n2. Personal life and interests take priority\n3. Maintains a healthy work-life balance\n4. Uses work as a tool to fund personal aspirations\n5. Prioritizes personal happiness and well-being\n6. Views work as a component of life, not the entire purpose\n7. Seeks meaningful employment that supports personal growth\n8. Allows time for relationships, hobbies, and personal development\n\nIn essence, \"living for work\" means letting work consume your life, while \"work for living\" means using work as a vehicle to support and enhance your life's overall quality and personal goals.\n\nThe healthier approach is generally considered to be \"work for living,\" which promotes better mental health, personal satisfaction, and holistic well-being.",
